The paper deals with auction theory, which is a subfield of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely category. The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The paper's focus on optimal revenue and incentive compatibility suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation) as additional categories. Finally, the paper's use of closed-form expressions and integration suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category.
